          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The photoneutron energy spectra were first",
                " corrected for counting losses (< 2%), and",
                " background was substracted. corrections for neutron",
                " scattering and absorption within the target were",
                " made with a monte-carlo method. the contribution",
                " of neutrons from other competing channels was",
                " assessed by comparing data taken at lower incident",
                " electron energies. the other neutron producing",
                " channels, contributing < 10% to the spectra, were",
                " substracted where necessary from the data."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The He-4(g,n)He-3 differential cross section has",
                " been simultaneously measured at five laboratory",
                " angles between 30 and 142 degrees, from threshold",
                " to 110 MeV. The asymmetry in the angular distribution",
                " from 24 to 70 MeV has been extracted and found to",
                " have sign changes at energies which are in accord",
                " with the previous experiments. The total photo-",
                " neutron cross section has been observed to be close",
                " to the known (g,p) cross section. From the energy",
                " dependence of the asymmetry coefficient a 2+ state",
                " in He-4 at energy of about 35 MeV has been confirmed."
              ]
            }
          ],
